    note right of Available
        IllegalStateException is thrown by setContents, getContents,
        getAvailableDataFlavors, isDataFlavorAvailable, and getData
        only when the clipboard is externally unavailable
        (e.g., held by another application). This is a platform
        condition, not an internal object state transition.
        No user-callable method changes the object's internal state.
    end note
